{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625149","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625149"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17011"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17011","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17011"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.72,0.03,0.13,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9701"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68236"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9701","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9701"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17011"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53693"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"5352"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"12757"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22834"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22840"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68236","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68236"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe British colonisation of Australia began in 1788 with the arrival of the First Fleet. This marked the start of systematic dispossession of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples from their lands, cultures, and traditional ways of life.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the concept of colonisation in the Australian context?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Establishment of British settlements with Indigenous consent","Invasion and dispossession of Indigenous peoples","Gradual integration of two distinct societies","Implementation of British governance systems","Development of agricultural and trading outposts"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInvasion and dispossession of Indigenous peoples\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes colonisation in Australia. This involved the forcible occupation of land, displacement of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, and imposition of British law and governance systems.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEstablishment of British settlements with Indigenous consent\u003C/strong\u003E - No treaties were signed and consent was not sought from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGradual integration of two distinct societies\u003C/strong\u003E - Colonisation involved forced assimilation rather than voluntary integration\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplementation of British governance systems\u003C/strong\u003E - While this occurred, it understates the violent nature of colonisation and displacement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDevelopment of agricultural and trading outposts\u003C/strong\u003E - This minimises the systematic nature of colonial occupation and its devastating impacts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe impacts of colonisation continue to affect Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples through intergenerational trauma, systemic inequities, and ongoing health disparities.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Colonisation refers to the invasion, dispossession and settlement of a land already inhabited by Indigenous peoples.","The colonisation of Australia by the British began in 1788 and resulted in widespread displacement of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples.","The impacts of colonisation continue to affect Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples\u0027 health and wellbeing today."],"references":["History: colonisation. Working with Indigenous Australians. Updated 2020. Available from: http://www.workingwithindigenousaustralians.info/content/History_3_Colonisation.html"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53693"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17011"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53693"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-09T15:28:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T15:29:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9701"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68236"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving in